  "prompt": "How does moon shine?",
  "response": "The moon shines as a result of reflecting sunlight. Although the moon does not produce its own light like the sun, its surface reflects the sunlight that hits it. This reflected light is what we see when we observe the moon from Earth. The brightness and the phase of the moon we observe depend on its position relative to the Earth and the sun. As the moon orbits the Earth, different portions of its surface are illuminated by the sun, leading to the various phases of the moon, from new moon to full moon and back again.",
